{
  "texts": [
    "Table 3 illustrates that different prompt types have different levels of effectiveness for different tasks and LLMs.",
    "We can also observe some general trends across the tasks and models.",
    "Prompt Optimization and EvaluationFor clinical sense disambiguation, the heuristic and prefix prompts consistently achieved the highest performance across all LLMs, significantly outperforming baselines such as BERT [30] and ELMO, with GPT-3.5 achieving an accuracy of 0.96, showcasing its advanced understanding of clinical context using appropriate prompting strategies.",
    "For biomedical evidence extraction, the heuristic and chain of thought prompts excelled across all LLMs in zero-shot setting.",
    "This indicates that these prompt types were able to provide enough information and constraints for the model to extract the evidence from the clinical note."
  ]
}